ce. Nevertheless, that=E2=80=99s the bet that the Ken Griffen-Witkoff class=
 appears to be making. And it=E2=80=99s the animating idea of my partner Ta=
ra Palmeri=E2=80=99s excellent story The Ron Revival ( https://puck.news/de=
santis-kissed-made-up-with-trump-what-now/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+S=
UBSCRIBERS+%285%2F25%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285=
%2F17%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=
=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), which focuses on the DeSantis long game and the ag=
e-old art of donor-class scheming.

Tara=E2=80=99s piece surfaces a perennial theme here at Puck: executive-cla=
ss Vulcan chess. And it wasn=E2=80=99t the only piece this week that covere=
d the terrain. Bill Cohan=E2=80=99s masterful story Starz Wars ( https://pu=
ck.news/lionsgate-bondholders-livid-over-studio-split-with-starz/?utm_campa=
ign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2F25%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backs=
tory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2F17%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=
=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) focuses on a particularly eg=
regious example of =E2=80=9Ccreditor-on-creditor violence=E2=80=9D at Lions=
gate, or what
happens when financially sophisticated investors re-cut a debt stack in the=
ir favor. It=E2=80=99s an example of conniving Wall Street restructuring, f=
eaturing former Treasury Secretary Steve Mnuchin, that ensures none of thes=
e guys ever eat lunch in Hollywood again.

Similarly, Lauren Sherman=E2=80=99s beguiling Weakened at Bernie=E2=80=99s =
( https://puck.news/why-michael-burke-stepped-down-from-lvmh-fashion-group/=
?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2F25%2F24%29&utm_content=
=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2F17%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&=
utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) delves further int=
o the latest LVMH enigma: the sudden sidelining of longtime executive and A=
rnault lieutenant Michael Burke. And Julia Alexander=E2=80=99s compelling e=
xplanation of the latest genre-defining streaming deal=E2=80=94Netflix to t=
he NFL: You Complete Me ( https://puck.news/netflix-to-the-nfl-you-complete=
-me/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2F25%2F24%29&utm_conte=
nt=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2F17%2F24%29&utm_medium=3Demail_actio=
n&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )=E2=80=94shows ho=
w this corporate union was lying in plain sight for years.

But if you only have time to read one piece this holiday weekend, I=E2=80=
=99d turn your attention to Marion Maneker=E2=80=99s scintillating Warhol, =
Basquiat & A $1.4 Billion Art Question ( https://puck.news/what-may-auction=
s-data-says-about-art-market/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2=
85%2F25%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2F17%2F24%29=
&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42=
abd12a ), which deftly describes the head-scratching that is taking place a=
t even the highest levels of the art market. Just like the DeSantis reposit=
ioning, it=E2=80=99s a useful reminder that people who have made their fort=
unes in one industry can=E2=80=99t
always predict what will happen in an adjacent one=E2=80=94a note that the =
AOL billionaire Ted Leonsis, who now owns a portfolio of professional sport=
s teams, sounds in a fascinating conversation with my partner John Ourand, =
entitled Kings of Leonsis ( https://puck.news/ted-leonsis-on-new-economics-=
of-sports-team-ownership/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2=
F25%2F24%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%285%2F17%2F24%29&utm=
_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd1=
2a ).

This is a common occurrence, and a micro-leitmotif within the work of my pa=
rtners. But it=E2=80=99s worth recalling as a regiment of ultra-wealthy ind=
ividuals, largely weaned from tech and finance, increasingly press their im=
primatur on our culture. That, in so many ways, is one of the great stories=
 of our time, and it=E2=80=99s precisely what you should expect from Puck.

Happy Memorial Day,
Jon

